sdesc: "KDE non-linear video editor"
ldesc: "Kdenlive is a free open-source video editor for GNU/Linux and 
FreeBSD, which supports DV, AVCHD (experimental support) and HDV 
editing. Kdenlive relies on several other open source projects, such as 
FFmpeg and MLT video framework. It was designed to answer all needs, 
from basic video editing to semi-professional work."
